<item>
 <title>In China and Beyond, Action Plans Provide a Path for Improving Building Efficiency</title>
 <link>http://www.chinafaqs.org/blog-posts/china-and-beyond-action-plans-provide-path-improving-building-efficiency</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-filefield field-field-image&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;img src=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Shenzhen_China_Buildings.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;160&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; class=&quot;imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default&quot;/&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-author&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Sifan Liu        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;This post &lt;a href=&quot;http://thecityfix.com/blog/china-beyond-action-plans-provide-path-improving-building-efficiency-sifan-liu/&quot;&gt;originally appeared&lt;/a&gt; on TheCityFix.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unique to China, Five-Year Plans (FYPs) are blueprints that central, state and local governments draft and implement to guide social and economic development. Since 1995, the national government has focused on energy efficiency in buildings in its FYPs, and sub-national governments have followed suit since 2000. Since then, many cities have released Building Energy Efficiency action plans as a sub-component of their FYPs. In fact, incorporating building energy efficiency action plans into FYPs is already a growing trend among many cities across China.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/blog-posts/china-and-beyond-action-plans-provide-path-improving-building-efficiency&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
 <category domain="http://www.chinafaqs.org/category/issue-areas/us-and-china-clean-tech-business-opportunities">The US and China- Clean Tech Business Opportunities</category>
 <category domain="http://www.chinafaqs.org/category/issue-areas/consumer-power-use">Consumer Power Use</category>
 <category domain="http://www.chinafaqs.org/category/issue-areas/energy-and-emissions-data">Energy and Emissions Data</category>
 <category domain="http://www.chinafaqs.org/category/issue-areas/energy-efficiency">Energy Efficiency</category>
 <category domain="http://www.chinafaqs.org/category/issue-areas/measurement-and-compliance">Measurement and Compliance</category>
 <category domain="http://www.chinafaqs.org/category/issue-areas/policy-and-governance">Policy and Governance</category>
